Right-click **Command Prompt** and select **Run as administrator**. 3. Type **ipconfig /release** in the command prompt. 4. Wait a few seconds for a reply that the IP address has been released. 5. Type **ipconfig /renew** in the command prompt. 6. Wait a few seconds for a reply that the IP address has been re-established. 7. Type **ipconfig /flushdns** in the command prompt. 8. Close the command prompt and attempt to make a connection. OPTIONAL: after you type ipconfig /flushdns you can try this command as well: 1. Type **netsh int ip reset** in the command prompt. 2. restart your computer for the changes to take effect and attempt a connection.
